Free Rides for Blind in Guangzhou
The first group of blind people, totalling 1,400, in this capital of
south China's Guangdong Province have received certificates from the
local government allowing them to ride free on the 161 lines of city
buses and 13 ferry routes.
The city has about 20,000 blind people, most of them capable of outdoor
activities.
The city government first issued free passes to blind people as early
as in July 1989, valid on 50 city bus and ferry lines.
